<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF107-925-354  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 925 354.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computergram International  Nov 30 1989 n1316* Full Text COPYRIGHT Apt Data Services 1989.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>ICL Espana represents Spain in Esprit modelling support.andM;</TITLE><DESCRIPT>Company:   ICL Espana S.A. (product development).andO;Topic:     SpainGraphics SystemsModeling of Computer SystemsPerformanceProject EngineeringUNIXCompatible Hardware.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>ICL ESPANA REPRESENTS SPAIN IN ESPRIT MODELLING SUPPORTandM;PROJECTICL's Spanish arm, ICL Espana SA, is to represent Spain in theEuropean General Research Programme, Esprit II, following the EuropeanCommunity Commission's approval of a new information technology projectwithin the research programme.andP;  ICL is to help develop an IntegratedModelling Support Environment, with the main object of offering a totallytransportable support environment for an integrated set of modelling toolsfor graphics workstations under Unix.andP;  The Integrated Environment willconcentrate mainly on performance modelling support as an integral part ofthe design process in numerous development areas of new generation computers.andO;The techniques will also be used in areas such as com-uter integratedmanufacture, communications networks, and information technology systemsdesign.andP;  The project is particularly important in the area of computerperformance modelling tools and techniques, given the general lack of unifiedanalysis standards here.andP;  ICL Espana has already started work on the projectwhich has a budget of $6.8m and should employ 50 people per year.andP;  ICL andits parent STC Plc already participate in 14 different projects under EspritII, and lead four of them.andO;</TEXT></DOC>